{"TopicId":123727,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Is there a way to make ofdset \u0026quot;unlimited\u0026quot;","CreatedByName":"TronX33","CreatedById":109784,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-10-25T03:30:23Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"TronX33","CreatedById":109784,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-10-25T03:30:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ESo yeah. While building a craft, I needed to offset something, but it could not go far enough. I heard of a mod for this, but A forum and google search turned up no results. Any help?\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-10-25T20:46:18Z\u0022 title=\u002210/25/2015 08:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 25, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by TronX33\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Van Disaster","CreatedById":58876,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-10-25T04:13:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYou\u0027re not going mad, I definitely remember a mod for that - I can\u0027t find it either though.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Yasmy","CreatedById":79995,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-10-25T08:37:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI have not tried this since before the offset tool, so maybe this won\u0027t work anymore, but try this: \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPlace the part. Save the ship under one name. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOffset the part in the direction you want. Save the ship under a second name.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECompare the geometry specifications of the two parts in the two ship save files.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhatever coordinate changed, keep changing it and reloading it in KSP until it is where you want it.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sebi.zzr","CreatedById":81294,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-10-25T09:04:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EMaybe you didn\u0027t look hard enough \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons